<div class="rules-container">
    <div class="rules-header">How to Pray Janazah Prayer</div>

    <div class="rules-section">
        <h3>What is Janazah Prayer?</h3>
        <p>The Janazah (funeral) prayer is a collective obligation (<strong>Fard Kifayah</strong>) for Muslims. It is a prayer without rukū‘ (bowing) or sujūd (prostration) and is performed standing. It is offered to seek forgiveness for the deceased Muslim.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="rules-section">
        <h3>Conditions for Janazah Prayer</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>The deceased must be a Muslim.</li>
            <li>The body must be washed, shrouded, and placed in front of the congregation.</li>
            <li>The congregation must face the Qiblah.</li>
            <li>Performed preferably in congregation.</li>
            <li>No wudu = no participation (must be in a state of purity).</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="rules-section">
        <h3>Structure of Janazah Prayer</h3>
        <p>The Janazah prayer consists of four <strong>Takbeerat</strong> (saying “Allahu Akbar”), standing only, and no physical movements.</p>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <strong>First Takbeer:</strong> Raise hands and say <strong>“Allahu Akbar”</strong>.
                <br>Recite <strong>Surah Al-Fatiha</strong> silently.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Second Takbeer:</strong> Say <strong>“Allahu Akbar”</strong>.
                <br>Recite <strong>Salawat (Durood Ibrahim)</strong>:
                <br>اللَّهُمَّ صَلِّ عَلَىٰ مُحَمَّدٍ وَعَلَىٰ آلِ مُحَمَّدٍ...
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Third Takbeer:</strong> Say <strong>“Allahu Akbar”</strong>.
                <br>Make <strong>Du‘a for the deceased</strong>. One common supplication:
                <blockquote>
                    اللَّهُمَّ اغْفِرْ لِحَيِّنَا وَمَيِّتِنَا... وَمَنْ أَحْيَيْتَهُ مِنَّا فَأَحْيِهِ عَلَى الْإِسْلَامِ
                </blockquote>
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Fourth Takbeer:</strong> Say <strong>“Allahu Akbar”</strong>.
                <br>You may make a short silent du‘a.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>End the prayer</strong> with one or two Tasleem (salutation) saying:
                <br><strong>“As-salaamu ‘alaykum wa rahmatullah”</strong> turning your head to the right.
            </li>
        </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="rules-section">
        <h3>Placement of the Body</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>If the deceased is a man, the Imam stands near the head of the body.</li>
            <li>If the deceased is a woman, the Imam stands near the middle of the body.</li>
            <li>Multiple bodies: place men closest to the Imam, women behind.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="rules-section">
        <h3>Important Sunnah Etiquettes</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Be in a state of Wudu and cleanliness.</li>
            <li>Keep your heart present and sincere when making Du‘a.</li>
            <li>Maintain silence during the prayer (no talking, cell phones, etc.).</li>
            <li>Attend the Janazah with the intention of reward and support for the deceased.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="note-box">
        <strong>Note:</strong> Janazah prayer is a mercy for the deceased. The more Muslims who attend and sincerely pray, the greater the reward for the deceased and the attendees.
    </div>
